  "text": "The Node.js ESM (ECMAScript Modules) loader and CommonJS-ESM interoperability system is implemented across multiple JavaScript files in lib/internal/modules/ and C++ binding files in src/.\n\n## Core ESM Loader Architecture\n\nThe entry point for ESM module loading is lib/internal/modules/run_main.js, which contains the executeUserEntryPoint() function that determines whether a module should be loaded as ESM or CommonJS using shouldUseESMLoader(). This function checks file extensions (.mjs), package.json type field, and experimental flags to decide the module type. The resolveMainPath() function resolves the actual file path to the entry point.\n\n## ModuleLoader Class\n\nThe core ModuleLoader class (lib/internal/modules/esm/loader.js) orchestrates the ESM loading pipeline. It manages:\n- Resolution: Uses defaultResolve() from lib/internal/modules/esm/resolve.js which implements the ESM resolution algorithm, handling bare specifiers, relative paths, and package exports via moduleResolve(), packageResolve(), and packageExportsResolve().\n- Loading: Delegates to defaultLoad() in lib/internal/modules/esm/load.js for fetching module source code.\n- Format Detection: Uses defaultGetFormat() from lib/internal/modules/esm/get_format.js to determine module format (module, commonjs, json, builtin, wasm).\n- Translation: The translators map in lib/internal/modules/esm/translators.js provides format-specific loaders for different module types.\n\n## Module Job Pipeline\n\nlib/internal/modules/esm/module_job.js defines ModuleJob and ModuleJobSync classes that manage the linking and evaluation pipeline. ModuleJob handles:\n- Link phase: Connects imported modules together via ModuleWrap::Link() in src/module_wrap.cc\n- Instantiation: Prepares the module for evaluation via ModuleWrap::Instantiate()\n- Evaluation: Executes module code via ModuleWrap::Evaluate()\n\n## CJS-ESM Interoperability\n\nlib/internal/modules/cjs/loader.js implements the CommonJS loader and includes the finalizeEsmResolution() function that bridges CJS-to-ESM resolution. This allows CommonJS modules to import ESM modules and ensures package.json exports configuration is properly resolved for both module systems.\n\n## Supporting Systems\n\n- Hooks System (lib/internal/modules/esm/hooks.js): Implements Hooks and HooksProxy classes for user-defined loader hooks (resolve, load, getFormat, etc.).\n- Module Map (lib/internal/modules/esm/module_map.js): ResolveCache and LoadCache classes cache resolution and loading results.\n- Fetch Module (lib/internal/modules/esm/fetch_module.js): Implements fetchModule() for remote module loading via HTTP/HTTPS.\n- Import Meta (lib/internal/modules/esm/initialize_import_meta.js): Initializes import.meta object with url and resolve.\n- Utilities (lib/internal/modules/esm/utils.js): compileSourceTextModule() compiles source text, initializeESM() initializes the ESM system.\n\n## Native C++ ModuleWrap Binding\n\nsrc/module_wrap.cc and src/module_wrap.h implement the ModuleWrap class that wraps V8's Module API. Key methods:\n- CompileSourceTextModule(): Compiles JavaScript source into a V8 module\n- ResolveModuleCallback(): Implements module resolution at the V8 level\n- Link(): Implements ES module linking\n- Instantiate()/InstantiateSync(): Prepares modules for evaluation\n- Evaluate()/EvaluateSync(): Executes module code and handles top-level await\n\nThe src/node_modules.cc file provides the native binding getNearestParentPackageJSONType() which is used to determine module type from package.json files.\n\n## Module Loading Chain\n\nThe complete chain is: executeUserEntryPoint() → shouldUseESMLoader() → ModuleLoader.import() → defaultResolve() → defaultLoad() → translators → ModuleJob → ModuleWrap::Link() → ModuleWrap::Evaluate().\n\nFor CommonJS interop, finalizeEsmResolution() in cjs/loader.js handles package.json exports resolution when CommonJS code needs to find ESM modules."
}

